      { text: "They have a power of attorney, but I'm not sure if it's durable", score: 0.5, status: "warn", explain: "If the document doesn't explicitly say 'durable,' it becomes worthless at the exact moment they need it — when they're incapacitated. This is the single most common POA mistake." },
